{
  "texts": [
    "A recall is a measure of the proportion of Positive image samples accurately classified as Positive compared to the total number of Positive image samples.",
    "It is a measure of how well the model can identify positive samples.",
    "The higher the recall, the more positive samples are detected (Aguiar et al. 2019; Xu et al. 2019).",
    "Average precision is defined as the weighted mean of precisions achieved at each threshold, with the increase in recall as the weight for each threshold:",
    "where P n and R n are the precision and recall at the nth threshold."
  ]
}